From e6589a4816dadee7014eb6238bdaf1acc4b80a93 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 20:40:22 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 02/25] Add batch-token registry to the external-runtime
 channel
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Opaque, never-recycled identities for update batches, replacing raw lane
exposure for external stores. Edge-triggered from the reconciler's own
bookkeeping (claim via getCurrentWriteBatch, pending via markRootUpdated,
finish via post-markRootFinished pendingLanes pruning, close at scheduling-
microtask end), so identities can never alias across lane-bit reuse and
work discarded by unmounts retires through the same edge as ordinary
commits. Tokens are minted lazily per batch (never per write); all edges
are integer/null checks when no token exists. Colliding claims on a live
lane reuse the token — an explicit merge, mirroring what React itself does.
unstable_getCurrentWriteBatch + onBatchRetired + included-batch arrays on
onRenderPassStart.
